enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve creating an unmodifiable version of a collection (a map in one case, an entry set in the other).
Both methods create unmodifiable versions of sets, which can be used to set up the state for testing the unmodifiableSortedMap method.
The unmodifiableEntrySet method returns an unmodifiable set of map entries, which can be used to verify the output of the unmodifiableSortedMap method.
The unmodifiableSet method returns an unmodifiable set, which can be used to verify the key set of the unmodifiableSortedMap method.
